HEADWORD: Misapprehension
<hw>Mis*ap`pre*hen"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
mistaking or mistake; wrong apprehension of one's meaning of a fact;
misconception; misunderstanding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misapprehensively</ent>⟦br⟧
